com.kaiserware.sailingrace

Class GPSLocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kaiserware.sailingrace.GPSLocation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.android.gms.common.api.GoogleApiClient.ConnectionCallbacks, com.google.android.gms.common.api.GoogleApiClient.OnConnectionFailedListener, com.google.android.gms.location.LocationListener

    public class GPSLocation
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.google.android.gms.common.api.GoogleApiClient.ConnectionCallbacks, com.google.android.gms.common.api.GoogleApiClient.OnConnectionFailedListener, com.google.android.gms.location.LocationListener
    Helper Class to fetch the GPS location, heading, and speed from the build-in location services utilizing the updated LocationManager's FusedLocationAPI which depends on GooglePlay Services. Both classes (GPSTracker and GPSlocation) are compatible for use in the SailingRace app. Created by Volker Petersen February 2016.

      • GPSLocation

                   long gpsUpdates,
                   int storeNumberLocations,
                   fifoQueueDouble COG,
                   fifoQueueDouble SOG,
                   int permit)
        GPS location, heading, and speed service
        Parameters:
        act - - Activity of the Calling Class
        gpsUpdates - - long minimum time (in milliseconds) between GPS updates
        storeNumberLocations - - int keepNumPositions: max GPS location history to compute average speed / heading
        COG - - fifQueueDouble holding Course Over Ground readings
        SOG - - fifQueueDouble holding Speed Over Ground readings
        permit - - int USER PERMIT CODE used in calling Class and this Class
